			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Sodium hydroxide (NaOH), also known as caustic soda or lye, is a corrosive white crystalline solid that contains the Na + ( sodium) cation and the OH − ( hydroxide) anion. It readily absorbs moisture until it dissolves. Sodium hydroxide is the most widely used industrial alkali and is often used in drain and oven cleaners. It is a highly versatile substance used in a variety of manufacturing processes. Sodium hydroxide is a co-product of chlorine production.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">氢氧化钠（NaOH）又称烧碱或碱液，是一种腐蚀性白色结晶固体，含有 Na +（钠）阳离子和 OH -（氢氧化）阴离子。它很容易吸收水分，直至溶解。氢氧化钠是应用最广泛的工业碱，常用于下水道和烤箱清洁剂。它是一种用途广泛的物质，可用于各种生产工艺。氢氧化钠是氯生产的副产品。</common:generalComment>
